# Testing Standards

## Stack
- **Unit/Integration**: Vitest (native Vite integration, fast, ESM-first)
- **Browser/E2E**: Playwright (browser-based testing, visual verification)
- **Coverage**: `@vitest/coverage-v8`, minimum **80%** lines + branches

## Test Organization
```
src/
  systems/
    resource-manager.ts
    resource-manager.test.ts    # colocated unit test
  scenes/
    BootScene.ts
tests/
  e2e/
    game-flow.spec.ts           # Playwright browser tests
```

## Unit Test Rules
- Colocate test files next to source: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`
- One `describe` block per function/class
- Test names describe behavior: `it("returns zero when no tiles are owned")`
- Use `beforeEach` for setup, never share mutable state across tests
- Mock external dependencies (network, DOM), never mock the unit under test

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — clear arrange/act/assert
describe("ResourceManager", () => {
  it("calculates income proportional to tile count", () => {
    const manager = new ResourceManager();
    manager.setTileCount(10);

    const income = manager.calculateIncome();

    expect(income).toBe(10 * BASE_INCOME_PER_TILE);
  });
});
```

## Browser Test Rules (Playwright)
- Use for visual verification, game flow, and interaction testing
- Tests run against the dev server (`npm run dev`)
- Take screenshots at key states for regression checks
- Keep browser tests focused — don't retest unit-level logic

## Coverage Requirements
- **80% minimum** on lines and branches — enforced in CI
- New features must include tests; PRs that drop coverage are blocked
- Game scenes may have lower unit coverage but must have browser test coverage

## What NOT to Test
- Phaser engine internals (trust the framework)
- Pure config objects
- Third-party library behavior
